				 Boys drown in school
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Purulia, Oct. 13: Three Class X students of the Ramakrishna Mission school here drowned this afternoon in a pond on the campus where bathing is prohibited .																								Police said the boys from Manipur  Gyanjit Singh, Dinabandhu Singh and M.N. Johan Singh  were preparing to return home as the school closed today for the Pujas.																								Gyanjit did not know how to swim. The other two tried to save him, but it appears that Gyanjit held on to his mates, a police officer said.																								Another classmate, Anirban Basu, raised the alarm. Monks and other officials of the mission brought them out of the water. Gyanjit was dead when the missions doctor saw him. The other two died on the way to Purulia Sadar Hospital. 
